About Kwakami Inu

The Kawakami Inu is not just any dog, its one of the rarest breeds in the world, originating from the mountains of Japan. With roots tracing back centuries, this breed has been admired for its loyalty, intelligence, and resilience. Unlike common breeds, the Kawakami Inu is scarce, cherished, and carries a cultural legacy that few others can match.

This rarity is more than symbolic - it defines the spirit of our token. Just as the Kawakami Inu breed is rare in the physical world, Kawakami Inu the token represents exclusivity and uniqueness in the digital world. Its not about being one of many, its about being one of the few, part of a pack that stands apart.

Owning Kawakami Inu isnt just holding a token; its becoming part of a lineage built on rarity, heritage, and strength.

How To Buy

Download metamask or your wallet of choice from the app store or google play store for free. Desktop users, download the google chrome extension by going to metamask.io.

Have ETH in your wallet to switch to $KAMI. If you dont have any ETH, you can buy directly on metamask, transfer from another wallet, or buy on another exchange and send it to your wallet.

Connect to Uniswap. Go to app.uniswap.org in google chrome or on the browser inside your Metamask app. Connect your wallet. Paste the $KAMI token address into Uniswap, select Kawakami Inu, and confirm. When Metamask prompts you for a wallet signature, sign.

Swap ETH for $KAMI. We have ZERO taxes so you dont need to worry about buying with a specific slippage, although you may need to use slippage during times of market volatility.
